Geologic time scale (GTS): history of Earth

=units
Eon: 100+ My
Era: 10-100 My
Period: 1-10 My
Epoch: 0.1-1 My
Age: 1-100 ky

=eons
Precambrian
- Hadean (4.5-4 By): formation of Earth and Moon
- Archean (4-2.5 Gy): Late Heavy Bombardment, bacteria
- Proterozoic (2.5-0.5 Gy): eukaryotes
Phanerozoic (0.5-0 Gy): life on land, mass extinctions

=Proterozoic periods
Paleo
- Siderian (2500-2300 My): Great Oxygenation Event
- Rhyacian (2300-2050 My): Huronian glaciation
- Orosirian (2050-1800 My)
- Statherian (1800-1600 My)
Meso
- Calymmian (1600-1400 My)
- Ectasian (1400-1200 My)
- Stenian (1200-1000 My)
Neo
- Tonian (1000-720 My): red and green algae, Rodinia supercontinent
- Cryogenian (720-635 My): Snowball Earth
- Ediacaran (635-540 My): jellyfish, sponges

=Phanerozoic eras and periods
Palaeozoic: trilobites
- Cambrian (540-485 My): molluscs, crustaceans
- Ordovician (485-444 My): corals, cephalopods
- Silurian (444-420 My): fish, myriapods
- Devonian (420-360 My): bony fish, ferns, trees
- Carboniferous (360-300 My): moss, insects, spiders, amphibians
- Permian (300-250 My): reptiles, sharks, beetles, conifers, Dimetrodon
Mesozoic: ammonites, dinosaurs, pterosaurs, cycads
- Triassic (250-200 My): ichthyosaurs, crocodiles, flies, Pangea supercontinent
- Jurassic (200-145 My): plesiosaurs, crabs, turtles, wasps, mammals, Archaeopteryx, Allosaurus, Stegosaurus, Diplodocus
- Cretaceous (145-66 My): mosasaurs, flowers, palms, marsupials, birds, bees, ants, Tyrannosaurus, Triceratops, Ankylosaurus
Cenozoic: butterflies, snakes, ungulates, carnivores, rodents, primates

=Cenozoic periods and epochs
Paleogene
- Paleocene (66-56 My): penguins, owls
- Eocene (56-34 My): whales, camels, horses, dogs, cats, pigs
- Oligocene (34-23 My): grasses
Neogene: mastodons
- Miocene (23-5 My): giraffes, deer, apes, hyenas
- Pliocene (5-2.5 My)
Quaternary: ice ages, humans
- Pleistocene (2.5-0.01 My): Smilodon, Woolly mammoth, Neanderthal
- Holocene
